<p>1.  The gate keepers are dead, period.  You can no longer stop information from getting out.  Now the propagandists are alive and well and I think that is the point you are actually making.  </p>
<p>2.  Um, Steven Hawking?  How fit physically is he?  There was a college football coach don&#8217;t remember his name but he was big time and remained a head coach after a stroke.  They propped  him up with a back board on the field, he would watch the team and his wife would read his lips and pass on his instructions.  He took his team to two bowl games and won both before retiring.  </p>
<p>Again I am not saying physical ability isn&#8217;t important, I am saying mental ability is MORE IMPORTANT.  I can break your leg, after that you won&#8217;t be running, jumping, climbing very well, your mind will still work.  </p>
<p>Now are mind and body one?  Too a large degree yep, again I get the point you are trying to make.  My point is if you rely on the phyical you are totally screwed in the end.  We all grow old and we all grow weak in time.</p>
